(this article continues to be updated. The time shown at the beginning of the paragraph is the update time for this article.)

###Italy

0800[587 new confirmed cases, 3,089 confirmed cases ]

According to the latest figures released by the Italian Ministry of Health at 18:00 local time on March 4, there are now 2,706 cases and 107 deaths. There were 587 new cases and 28 new deaths compared with 18:00 on March 3. The cumulative total number of confirmed cases was 3,089. Italy's Health Ministry announced on the 4th that since the 3rd, the Civil Protection Department has "red zone" (Lombardy's 10 towns and a town in Veneto) residents have distributed 25,000 medical masks. At the same time, 400,000 FFP2 and FFP3 European standard grade protective masks were provided to medical personnel throughout Italy.

###Brazil

0800[ the number of confirmed suspected cases in Brazil jumped to 531]

At a press conference on March 4 local time, Ministry of Health Louis said that as of 17:00 p.m. on March 4, Brazil had confirmed one new case of pneumonia, the patient, a 46-year-old Colombian male living in Sao Paulo, recently visited Spain, Italy, Austria and Germany and returned to Sao Paulo to seek medical attention when he developed symptoms. In addition, one patient tested positive for NCP NUCLEIC ACID and is currently undergoing re-examination. If confirmed, he will be diagnosed as NCP.

The number of suspected cases in Brazil has jumped to 531, from 315 previously ruled out. The two previously confirmed cases of NCP in Brazil, both of which were confirmed as imported cases on 26 February and 29 February respectively, are both são Paulo residents with recent travel to Italy.

###France

0800[ LOUVRE REOPENS ON MARCH 4TH ]

Nearly three-quarters of the 9.6 m visitors to the Louvre last year came from abroad. In addition to the Louvre, the ban will affect hundreds of theatres and thousands of cultural events in France, after the government announced it was cancelling all major events involving more than 5,000 people in a closed environment.

0800[257 newly diagnosed cases of new coronary pneumonia ]

France has reported 45 new cases of newly diagnosed pneumonia, bringing the total to 257, the Yogi Bear reported.

###The United States

0830[153 confirmed cases, 11 deaths ]

CNN, citing the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and state and local governments, has confirmed 153 cases of new coronary pneumonia in the United States, including 11 deaths and 8 cures.

0800. We have a code red in Los Angeles

Authorities in the Los Angeles area have declared a state of emergency and say they have found six new cases of pneumonia in the past 48 hours, CNBC reported.

A total of seven people in the Los Angeles area have been reported to have newly diagnosed pneumonia.

0800(11 deaths from 126 confirmed cases of MEIXIN PNEUMONIA)

On March 4 local time, a total of 126 cases of new coronary pneumonia were confirmed in 13 states. The death toll has risen to 11, with eight people from the same county in Washington state and five linked to a nursing home in a Seattle suburb called life care.

###Germany

0800[ a cumulative total of 344 newly diagnosed cases of pneumonia in Germany ]

According to statistics published by the European Times at 20:00 local time on March 4, as of 20:00 local time on March 4, Germany has a total of 344 confirmed cases of new pneumonia, confirmed cases in a day increased by more than 100 cases.

German 2020 industrial show in Hanover postponed to July

###Algeria

0800[17 confirmed cases, 16 infected by the same person ]

According to the Algerian Ministry of Health, population and health reform on March 4, the same day, Algeria added 9 new cases of new pneumonia confirmed cases, the country has a cumulative total of 17 confirmed cases. Except the first case, the other 16 cases were all from the same source of infection.

Information shows that Algeria's second and third confirmed cases of a mother and daughter living in Brida province. Between 14 and 21 February, an 83-year-old French relative who had stayed at his home returned to France feeling unwell and tested positive upon his return. The two women were diagnosed on March 1, and all 14 infected patients in Afghanistan have had contact with the two women since.

###India

0800[29 confirmed cases including 16 Italian tourists ]

Indian media reported on the evening of 4, the satellite city of Gurugram near New Delhi that night confirmed a new case of pneumonia, the case recently returned from a holiday in Italy, symptoms after medical treatment, blood samples tested positive, confirmed infection. Earlier in the day, the Indian Ministry of Health confirmed that a total of 23 confirmed cases, including 15 Italian tourists, appeared in India on the 4th.

Premier Molde FK, Interior Minister Amit Shah and other dignitaries that day urged the public not to panic, to minimize the gathering activities to prevent the spread of the epidemic.

###Sweden

0800[ a total of 52 newly confirmed cases of coronary pneumonia in Sweden (22)]

On the evening of March 4 local time, Swedish television station (SVT) reported that 22 new cases of coronary pneumonia were confirmed in Sweden in one day, bringing the total number of confirmed cases in Sweden to 52.

###Spain

0800(193 cases of newly diagnosed pneumonia in Spain are most severe in the capital Madrid)

As of 6:00 PM local time on the 4th, 193 cases of new pneumonia were confirmed in Spain, of which the capital Madrid remained the most serious, rising to 76 cases. Of these patients, 3 were children. At present, the Spanish government has not considered the closure of schools to impose suspension measures.

###WHO

0800[ a total of 12668 cases of newly diagnosed pneumonia outside China ]

As of 10:00 am (17:00 China Standard Time) on 4 March Central European time, a total of 12,668 cases and 214 deaths had been confirmed outside China in 76 countries, according to the WHO's daily report on the condition of new coronary pneumonia.

###IMF

0830[ IMF  and World Bank to hold 'virtual' meetings in spring ]

A number of related events were held during the conference, attracting a large number of officials, journalists and representatives of private enterprises. According to official figures, about 10,000 people attended. As advised by the public health sector, such large-scale meetings are prone to clustering of viral infections and should be avoided as much as possible.

0800[ providing up to $50 billion in response to new crown pneumonia outbreak ]

The International Monetary Fund (IMF) announced Thursday that it will provide up to $50 billion to help member countries cope with the new outbreak of pneumonia.

IMF Managing Director Georgieva said the $50 billion would be quickly channelled through emergency financing to low income countries and emerging economies in need. Of that, $10 billion will be provided to the poorest countries through interest-free loans.
